column3: “Tried 3 times, even mixed with CBD (which usually calms my anxiety), but still was a nervous wreck. It's not a bad strain by any means. It's just not for my body.”

“I need to find more of this stuff! I'm definitely wrecked right now as cheesy as that sounds. Super connected and energetically wavy. Love the sativa, great strain for social situations with great friends.”
“Fast acting, easy to light, it doesn't smell or taste horrible, and it provides an easy and pleasant high.”
“Love the strong pungent smell of cheese. Some real good med. great high and the exhale is smooth. A must try!”
“very relaxed weed, and steady high to do things.smells like cheese too”
“Looks Good, smokes Great! Good for no sleep nights or simply needing to relax on the couch. Smooth flavor.”

“Tried this for the first time tonight and was very happy with it. 
Medium density, sticky buds with a strong, very dank smell.
A bit of a creeping up high for me but very relaxing and calming. The tail end of the high really helped with my insomnia.

Negatives: It did give me dry mouth worse than some other hybrids but other than that no negative effects for me.”
“Smell is amazing. Buds look great. Unfortunately, this one made me anxious and paranoid. Next time, I will mix it with 30% Sour Tsunami to tame it down a little”

“TASTE LIKE CHEESE SMELLS LIKE CHEESE ONE OF  FIRST STRAINS WHERE IT ACTUALLY TASTE LIKE THE NAME OOOWEEEE 😩🧀🚜

while smoking on some of these you will have that cheese taste in your mouth so if you dont like cheese this isnt the strain for you top notice high i can take about 3 pulls n be high already one l lasted me till the next day all n all top notch strain”

“Love cheese!

Pungent smell of feet just like cheese it produces a distinct aroma with a sweet and earthy notes.  As I mentioned being a fan of cheese I can say that U.K. Cheese and cheese #1 weren't as enjoyable or as potent as this nice hybrid of train wreck and cheese. Will definitely smoke again as long as it's available also would recommend Blue Cheese strain for those who enjoyed it as much as I.”

“Awesome strain, perfect blend of indica and sativa effects. I consumed using a nice Cheeswreck wax and and hit right away with the trainwreck-y sativa side while the Cheese indica rolls in after a little to calm it all down. Flavor is great, my pheno leans a bit towards the lemon from the trainwreck, but does have a flavorful cheese-y exhale. Medical properties are great, is apatite stimulating and relieves aches and...”
“nice weeed”

“Great Smoke! Nice taste, but a little rough inhale. Has a very pungent aroma and taste. The high starts out with with an aware, talkative state, then it mellows into a dizzy, sleepy state. A nice smoke if you're home with friends.”
“This potent strain is one of the most memorable I've smoked. The powerful sativa dominant effects left me in one of the best moods of my life. I would recommend this strain to all smokers.”

“Takes a longer than other statins to settle in, the high definitely creeps up on ya outta no where, this would not be good for someone who gets nervous or anxious/paranoid easily w cannabis. For me though I feel good, chill, vibey, music sounds better, I suck at Xbox now though lol. Smells just like Cheesecake, idk if other cuts are as dense as mine but the nugs are the densest I have ever had in 2 years, an eighth n...”
“Wonderful feeling this gave me i was happy an relaxed”

“TASTE LIKE CHEESE SMELLS LIKE CHEESE ONE OF  FIRST STRAINS WHERE IT ACTUALLY TASTE LIKE THE NAME OOOWEEEE 😩🧀🚜

while smoking on some of these you will have that cheese taste in your mouth so if you dont like cheese this isnt the strain for you top notice high i can take about 3 pulls n be high already one l lasted me till the next day all n all top notch strain”
“nice weeed”
“Always love a good cheese strain... this one is also one of my favorites.  It seemed to creep up on me a little, good relaxation.”
“Wonderful feeling this gave me i was happy an relaxed”
“Full body high, clouds the mind and makes everything heavy”
“A little harsh. Interesting smell. Doesn't kick in right away. More of a head high. Quite potent. I would give it a 4 if not for the taste.”
“Pretty solid strain, doesn't have the strongest smell but once grinded up the aromas really come out of cheese and pungent sweet smell.”

“more indica dominant than sativa in my opinion.
Also created immediate nasal congestion for me”

“I love this strain one of my favourite cheese cross, as I'm from the UK we get alot of different cheese variations mostly smoke exodus cheese so it's always nice to see a bit of cheesewreck flower I rate this a 5 as it top of my list for bedtime smoke”
“Great stuff”
“Picked this strain up from HC. I am very familiar with both cheese and train wreck and this is a great cross. Excellent daytime sativa, easy to get things done. Nice smell and taste.”

“Floratec(h) Nutrients, This strain grew like a Sativa with Indica influences, leaves started off wide like an Indica but later when switched to flowering, began too spread and thin out.

This strain loves to feed and if left without for about  week it will show quick signs of Nitrogen def. So pay attention to your feeding schedule and how it's doing.

The high isn't overwhelming whatsoever but depending on how yo...”
“Tasted like cheese,watched impractical jokers and laughed through the whole show,nice work”
“love cheese hate wreck”

“If you like a good old funky queso all up in your nostrils that will also get you abnormally hyped at the same time, let the cheese wreck you. Crazy trichomes wrapped hairy buds with a stank unlike anything else. Give caution the middle finger and have 2 bowls. And prepare to launch”
“2nd time smoking this and it's better this time, but I still don't know if this strain is for me. Seems to bring out my anxiety.”
“Nice medically predictable high with not too much lethargy but slight couch lock". reduces anxiety and depression levels to manageable levels.”"
“Pretty solid strain, doesn't have the strongest smell but once grinded up the aromas really come out of cheese and pungent sweet smell.”
“Strong but smooth inhale, and gives a heavy head high. Recommend it for frequent smokers. A”

“more indica dominant than sativa in my opinion.
Also created immediate nasal congestion for me”
“A little harsh. Interesting smell. Doesn't kick in right away. More of a head high. Quite potent. I would give it a 4 if not for the taste.”
“Full body high, clouds the mind and makes everything heavy”
“Was a little harsh,  tough not to choke on it.  Looked like it was grown outdoor.  5/10”
“Strong sativa high that calms down over time into a sort of relaxation. Great for day or night use”
“Not a fan of the smell but it doesn't taste horrible. Potent and relatively fast acting. I was a little irritated for some reason.”
“Every time I hear the word cheese" from my dealers my eyes get a bit watery. Any type of cheese weed is my favorite and this does the name justice.”"

“Sativa speed freaks, this is your flower. I picked up this strain from Uncle Ike's, grown by Gecko Growers. Tastes great, and gives you that heady, fun body buzz you're looking for when you're doing hiking or biking. This isn't the stuff you spark up when you're looking to unwind, but definitely more for socializing and working out.”
“Got me wrecked, eat some cheese”

“Personal favorite, I can't get enough of that cheese smell! Tastes great too. It creeps up and you end up with a nice long high. It also has some pretty decent arousing effects of you're with your partner. Nice bud to keep you awake but eventually helps you wind down. Had no problem driving and it eliminated my elbow pain. My only complaint is the flower itself isn't too attractive but that isn't a strong enough reas...”
“Took a bit to hit, but landed an even and happy high. Very potent.”

“Happy. Giddy. Euphoric. Been struggling with depression and this strains makeup has done wonders for the heaviness I've had the past few days in my mood. It only had .44% thc but had 19.46% thc-a and .56% Cbd. For a total of 17.4% thc. As someone who pays attention, though not closely to percentages, I was thoroughly surprised by the entire head and body high I got from just a couple small tokes. A little goes a long...”

“Even the shake of this strain gives Sour D a run for its money. And this strain easily beats out ak-47/48, it made both of those strains look like a joke! Its an Indica Dominant hybrid (I want to say 70/30) and a personal favorite.”
“Picked some up from Releaf Lansing and was not disappointed. I couldn't even make it through a whole joint. Cerebral high”

“I grabbed this because it was cheap , to try it out. At first I was unimpressed with the flavour, kinda like a bit of cheese dragged through the dirt ..But as it settled in I found myself chatty and happy, chill and relaxed...cant complain about that”

“so I tried the trainwreck an had to try the cheese wreck,  very very dank cheese smell, very sticky dense buds. the tast of this strain is awesome,  the trainwreck an the cheese put togher is second to none. extremely intense high that will keep you in a cheese haze for hours! don't pass this one up, great for my nerve damage and pain.”
“This is amazing total body buzz and felt no pain and I have tons of that highly recommend it for chronic pain”
“this bud gives you a really funny high effect”
“Definitely lives up to its name and effects. Sneaky strain”
